# Git and GitHub Workflow

## Creating Commits

1.  Check for changed files using `git status | cat`.
2.  Create a commit using `git add .` and `git commit -m "message"`.
3.  Write a brief message describing the changes, either per file or for all changes if minor.

## Creating Pull Requests

When asked to create a PR, follow this process (assuming GitHub CLI is authenticated):

1.  `git status | cat` - Check for uncommitted changes.
2.  `git add .` - Stage changes (if needed).
3.  `git commit -m "commit message"` - Commit changes (if needed).
4.  `git push` - Push changes to the remote repository (if needed).
5.  `git branch | cat` - Check the current branch.
6.  `git log main..[current_branch] | cat` - Log changes specific to the current branch relative to main.
7.  `git diff --name-status main | cat` - Check changed files relative to main.
8.  `gh pr create --title "Your Title Here" --body "Your single-line PR description here. Do not include newlines."` - Create the pull request.
